The course supports students' professional development by creating opportunities to integrate and practice knowledge acquired during the studies in the university. As a result of video analysis, video training, microteaching and simulation the course creates opportunities to analyse and therefore to give an adequate evaluation to his/her knowledge, skills, and attitudes concerning the following domains: communication, designing learning and instruction, teaching. In addition, domain- and subject-competences and didactics are taken into account.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course has three main goals that should be achieved jointly with the courses of the base module and continuous pedagogical traineeship: 1)	to support student's improvement to be a teacher by creating continuous opportunities in the university to associate theoretical knowledge with teacher's practical activities;  2)	to create opportunities to practice what is acquired in different base module courses and domain- and subject-didactics courses before  starting traineeship in an educational institution; 3)	to create opportunities to practice what is acquired in different base module courses and domain- and subject-didactics courses after completing a traineeship in an educational institution in order to complement experiences gained from the traineeship.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1)	is able to analyze on the basis of videos to what extent is the educational environment safe, supporting the involvement of every student and enables the students to feel success; 2)	notices on the basis of videos students with educational special needs and knows how to support their learning; 3)	is aware of the communication skills and good custom necessary to communicate with different groups of people; 4)	has gained the primary experience to integrate knowledge, skills and attitudes acquired in different basic module, domain- and subject-courses.
